  <synopsis><code mime="text/x-gjs">
function trylock(): Boolean {
    // Gjs wrapper for g_mutex_trylock()
}
  </code></synopsis>
  <p>Tries to lock <code>mutex</code>. If <code>mutex</code> is already locked by another thread,
it immediately returns <code>false</code>. Otherwise it locks <code>mutex</code> and returns
<code>true</code>.</p>  <p><link xref="GLib.Mutex"/> is neither guaranteed to be recursive nor to be
non-recursive.  As such, calling <link xref="GLib.Mutex.lock"/> on a <link xref="GLib.Mutex"/> that has
already been locked by the same thread results in undefined behaviour
(including but not limited to deadlocks or arbitrary return values).</p>

